AVEN2030 |website=Zalmhaven2030.nl |date= |accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref>\n|{{convert|212|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|2021 \n|Under construction\n|-\n|3\n|The Baltimore / Peter Stuyvesant Building<ref>{{cite web|author=Jan van Helleman |url=http://www.nieuws.top010.nl/peter-stuyvesant-building |title=Peter Stuyvesant Building - Nieuwbouw Architectuur Rotterdam |website=Nieuws.top010.nl |date=2016-12-23 |accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref>\n|{{convert|190|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|undetermined \n|On hold\n|-\n|4\n|The Dutch Windwheel\n|{{convert|164|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|2025\n|In development \n|-\n|5\n|[[Havana (building)|Havana]] / The Sax <ref name=\"top1\">{{cite web|author=Jan van Helleman |url=http://www.nieuws.top010.nl/havana-philadelphia-rotterdam |title=Havana - Philadelphia woontorens Rotterdam |website=Nieuws.top010.nl |date=2016-12-23 |accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref>\n|{{convert|154|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|2020\n|Approved\n|-\n|6\n|[[Cool Tower]]<ref>{{cite web|author=Jan van Helleman |url=http://www.nieuws.top010.nl/cooltower-rotterdam |title=CoolTower Rotterdam |website=Nieuws.top010.nl |date=2016-12-23 |accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref>\n|{{convert|150|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|2020\n|Under construction\n|-\n|7\n|[[Baan toren]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ad.nl/dossier-rotterdam/nieuwe-toren-in-rotterdam-wordt-smalste-van-europa~ad420e32/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-12-09 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201110655/http://www.ad.nl/dossier-rotterdam/nieuwe-toren-in-rotterdam-wordt-smalste-van-europa~ad420e32/ |archivedate=1 December 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=\u010ce\u0161tina |url=https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/plannen-gepresenteerd-voor-slankste-woontoren-van-europa-van-dam |title=Plannen gepresenteerd voor slankste woontoren van Europa |publisher=LinkedIn |date=2016-11-29 |accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref>\n|{{convert|150|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|2019\n|In development \n|-\n|8\n|The Terraced Tower <ref>{{cite web|url=http://provast.nl/projecten/boompjes/ |title=The Terraced Tower - Provast |website=Provast.nl |date= |accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref>\n|{{convert|110|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|2019\n|Under construction\n|-\n|9\n|[[Philadelphia (building)|Philadelphia]] / The Sax <ref name=\"top1\" />\n|{{convert|75|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|2020\n|Approved\n|-\n|10\n|The Muse<ref>https://themuseofrotterdam.nl</ref>\n|{{convert|74|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|2018\n|Under construction\n|-\n|11\n|De Metropool<ref>{{cite web|author=Jan van Helleman |url=http://www.nieuws.top010.nl/woontoren-kruiskade-rotterdam |title=De Metropool woontoren Kruiskade Rotterdam |website=Nieuws.top010.nl |date= |accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref>\n|{{convert|70|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|2020\n|Approved\n|-\n|12\n|Rotta Nova <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.overhd.nl/rottanova |title=Rottanova |website=Overhd.nl |date= |accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref>\n|{{convert|70|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|2020\n|On hold\n|-\n|13\n|Bright <ref>http://www.cobouw.nl/bouwbericht/1646121-bright-nieuwe-blikvanger-voor-hart-oude-rotterdam</ref>\n|{{convert|70|m|ft|abbr=values}}\n|2019\n|Approved\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of tallest buildings in the Netherlands]]\n* [[List of tallest structures in the Netherlands]]\n* [[List of tallest buildings in Amsterdam]]\n* [[List of tallest buildings in Haaglanden]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of buildings and structures in the Netherlands|Tallest in Rotterdam]]\n[[Category:Lists of tallest buildings in the Netherlands|Rotterdam]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Rotterdam|*]]\n[[Category:Skyscrapers in the Netherlands|*]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}}\n[[File:Erasmusbrug seen from Euromast.jpg|thumb|right|300px|[[Kop van Zuid]], viewed from the [[Euromast]]]]\n\n[[File:Skyline Rotterdam from Schiebroek.jpg|thumb|right|300px|The skyline of Rotterdam, viewed from [[Schiebroek]]]]\n\n[[Rotterdam]], the second most populous city in the [[Netherlands]], is home to 352 completed high-rises,<ref name=\"emporis1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.emporis.com/city/100760/rotterdam-netherlands/type/3/18 |title=Rotterdam |publisher=Emporis |date= |accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref> 36 of which are higher than {{convert|100|m|ft}}. The tallest building in Rotterdam is the [[Maastoren]], which rises {{convert|165|m|ft}}.<ref name=maastoren>{{Ctbuh|5559|Maastoren}}</ref> The 44 storey skyscraper also stands as the highest building in the [[Netherlands]] and the [[Benelux]].<ref name=maastoren/>\n\nRotterdam is well known as the high-rise city of the [[Netherlands]]. The city is therefore often called \"[[Manhattan]] at the [[Meuse]]\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.holland.com/global/tourism/architecture-rotterdam.htm# |title=Architecture Rotterdam - Tourism in the Netherlands |website=Holland.com |date=2017-02-09 |accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref> because a large amount of skyscrapers is standing close to the river [[Meuse]], especially at [[Kop van Zuid]]. Rotterdam has a rich history in high-rises, dating back to 1897 with the completion of \"Het [[Witte Huis]]\". This office building was at that time the tallest skyscraper in Europe.<ref>{{cite web|author=Jan van Helleman |url=http://www.top010.nl/html/het_witte_huis.htm |title=Het Witte Huis Rotterdam - Nieuwbouw Architectuur Rotterdam |website=Top010.nl |date=2016-12-23 |accessdate=2017-02-24}}</ref> Rotterdam is famous because of its characteristic skyline, and its world-wide reputation for innovative architecture.\nThe city is standing in the European SkylineTop together with [[Frankfurt]], [[Milan]], [[London]], [[Madrid]], [[Paris]], [[Warsaw]] and [[Moscow]]. Over 30 new high-rise projects are being developed at the moment.<ref name=\"emporis1\"/>\n\n==Buildings==\nThe listed heights are the constructive heights of the building. Architectonic and functional masts are only shown here for comparison.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!  \n! Name\n! Height<br />{{nowrap|[[Metre|m]] ([[Foot (unit)|ft]])}}\n! 